Reasoning: The paper proposes a new bibliometric index that takes into account the complete list of cited publications, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. Specifically, cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are likely sub-categories as they deal with the organization and retrieval of information, including bibliographic data. cs.CY (Computational Geometry) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are also possible sub-categories as they often involve the analysis and evaluation of research output. Finally, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is another possible sub-category as it deals with the study of networks and their properties, which can be related to the analysis of citation networks.
